@startuml Activity_5_FamilyMember
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam activityFontSize 14
skinparam arrowFontSize 13
skinparam swimlaneBorderThickness 2

title Activity Diagram 5 — Manage Family Members

|Homeowner|
start
:Log in to system;
:Navigate to Household Management;
:Select Add Family Member;
:Enter member name, email, and role;
:Define device access permissions\n(which devices the member can control);

|Mobile / Web App|
:Validate form inputs;
if (Form valid?) then (yes)
    :Send add member request to API Gateway;
else (no)
    :Display validation errors;
    stop
endif

|API Gateway|
:Validate Homeowner authentication token;
:Verify requester has Homeowner role;
if (Authorized?) then (yes)
    :Route to User and Preference Service;
else (no)
    :Return 403 Forbidden;
    |Mobile / Web App|
    :Display permission error;
    stop
endif

|User & Preference Service|
:Check if email already registered in system;
if (Email exists in system?) then (yes)
    :Link existing account to household;
    :Apply assigned permissions;
else (no)
    :Create new pending account;
    :Store assigned role and permissions;
    :Send invitation email via Notification Service;
endif

|Notification Service|
:Dispatch invitation email to new member;

|New Family Member|
:Receive invitation email;
if (Accepts invitation?) then (yes)
    :Click invitation link;
    :Set account password;
else (no)
    :Invitation expires after 48 hours;
    stop
endif

|User & Preference Service|
:Activate family member account;
:Propagate device permissions\nto Device Management Service;

|Device Management Service|
:Update access control list\nfor all assigned devices;
:Store per-member permission records in database;

|Mobile / Web App|
:Display updated household member list to Homeowner;

|Homeowner|
:Review and confirm member permissions;
if (Permissions need adjustment?) then (yes)
    :Edit member permissions;
    :Resubmit updated permissions;
else (no)
    :Member onboarding complete;
endif
stop

@enduml
